ation to achieve normalization, peace and security on the other. In view of this conflict-laden bi-national reality, the Palestinian question is identified as the Achilles' heel of Jewish statehood in the Land of Israel. Thus, Zionist Israel and the Question of Palestine provides a fresh, innovative, critical and yet accessible perspective on one of the most controversial issues in contemporary history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aArab-Israeli conflict. 0aZionism. 4aIsrael. 4aNahostkonflikt. 4aZionismus. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z97831107195430 cEPUBz97831104956450 cprintz978311049663540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110498806zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110498806zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110498806.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3 DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA